{panel:bgColor=#e7f4fa}
  *NOTE:* This suggestion is for *Confluence Server*. Using *Confluence Cloud*? [See the corresponding suggestion|http://jira.atlassian.com/browse/CONFCLOUD-5158].
  {panel}

A confirm page should be shown when restoring any kind of backup (space or site), to inform the user of exactly what is going to happen, and to allow them to back out.

Ideally, there would be one page for a space backup/export, which would identify the space key being restored (and whether the space already exists), and a note that it won't overwrite the rest of the site. A second confirm page would be displayed for site backups, which would clearly say that all existing content will be deleted, and the content and users from the backup will replace it.

{panel:bgColor=#e7f4fa}
  *NOTE:* This suggestion is for *Confluence Server*. Using *Confluence Cloud*? [See the corresponding suggestion|http://jira.atlassian.com/browse/CONFCLOUD-5140].
  {panel}

I think the full screen mode idea is a really good one because it is very difficult to manage the two scrollbars when editing, and it is annoying that you can't get the edit area to increase in height. I would really like to see the feature added to the Wiki markup editor too because the problems are just the same there.

It would be really useful to be able to pass an arbitrary list of issues to the 'jiraissues' macro so that they could be shown in a JIRA results table. I'm imagining something like:

  {jiraissues:issues=CONF-1000,CONF-2000,CONF-9999}

There are situations where the relationship between the issues is already in JIRA (say all the subtasks of an issue, or all the linked issues of a certain type such as 'depends on') so maybe providing the ability to show these kinds of results would be an alternative. But I find that there are often just a handful of issues that are related for some reason that I want to list on a page.

The usage of the 'upload' option in the attachment macro has no influence. It shows exact the same way as when you leave this parameter: There is no link or something else where you can upoad a attachment.

See attached screen-shot which is the result of following command:
{attachments:upload=true|old=true}

{tasklist:Tasklist Hans}
Application identity und user identity im Batch als Default setzen
Client Version Parameter beim Ausführen der Action
{tasklist}

If an item of the tasklist contains an umlaut, it's state can't be switched. So item1 in the example above can be switched, not so item2.

